        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 4:44PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gold Hill, or 8 miles northeast of Dillwyn, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

Locations impacted include...
Cumberland, Cartersville, Trenholm, Sunnyside, Lakeside Village,
Trents Mill, Ashby, Oak Forest, Clinton, Tamworth, Whiteville, Grays
Siding, Bear Creek Lake State Park, and Trenton Mills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
